From Gonubie to Motherwell, Elliotdale to Makhanda, Covid-19 has spread rapidly across the Eastern Cape, with confirmed cases now at 32. South Africa now has 1,686 cases, with 12 deaths tied to the disease. Below is a list of the locations of those infected with the coronavirus from the first 31 cases. The location of the 32nd person who tested positive was still to be confirmed at the time of publication. In the public interest, none of our coronavirus news coverage will be behind our paywall. It is available free for all to read. If you would like to support our mission of delivering award-winning, independent local news, please consider taking out a subscription by clicking here.